<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-513-951  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 513 951.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  August 13 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>New product: new version of Australian text retrieval software.andO;(Odyssey Development's Isys 2.0) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>McNamara, Sean.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Odyssey Development (product introduction).andO;Product:   Isys 2.0 (Search software) (product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionInformation Storage and RetrievalSoftware packages.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>NEW PRODUCT: New Version Of Australian Text Retrieval Software SYDNEY,AUSTRALIA, 1990 AUG 13 (NB) - Australian software house, Odyssey Development,has announced version 2.0 of its text-retrieval software, Isys.andP;  This versionof the software will be made available internationally.andM;Isys has been on the market in Australia since 1988, and won the 1989Australia Computer Society's Software Product of the Year Award.andP;  Odysseyhopes to repeat Isys' success in the international market, and hasincorporated many user- suggested features into Isys 2.0 to help achievethis.andP;  Features added or enhanced in Isys 2.0 include: increase in indexingand updating speed by a factor of six; context sensitive help; &quot;dynamicdocument activation,&quot; enabling users to open their word-processor with thedocument they have found; a print facility for searched documents; Windows3.0 compatibility; and more efficient use of computer resources (the programrequires 20 percent less memory and 30 percent less disk space than previousversions).andM;Isys 2.0 is distributed in Australia through Sourceware, and retail pricesare AUS$525 for the single-user version and AUS$995 for the network starterkit.andP;  Upgrade cost is AUS$135 for registered users.andP;  Pricing and distributiondetails for overseas are yet to be announced.andM;(Sean McNamara/19900813/Press Contact: Mark Reiss, phone in Australia+61-2-965 7250)</TEXT>